text.section:
An assessment of financial institution franchise tax, public service company franchise tax, income tax, or estate tax may be made at any time if:
a false return is filed with the intent to evade the tax;
a willful attempt is made to evade the tax;
a return is not filed as required under Title 7, Title 8, or Title 10 of this article;
an amended estate tax return is not filed as required under Title 7 of this article;
an incomplete return is filed; or
a report of federal adjustment is not filed within the period required under § 13-409 of this title.
